tracker_name: Reading a short text such as a mobile phone text message
Standing up for approx. 5 minutes e.g. while queuing or while cooking
Using the toilet (not bedpan or bedside commode)
Going to a shop for groceries
Focusing on a task for approx. 2 hours continuously
Physical activity with increased heart rate for approx. 15 min
Staying in a noisy environment (shopping mall café or open plan office) for approx. 1 hour
Managing a full working day (non-physical work such as office work classes or lectures)
Walking a short distance indoors from one room to another
Participating in organized leisure activities such as classes sports etc.
Having a conversation for approx. 5 minutes
Participating in a dinner party party or family event
Staying in a room with normal lighting without sunglasses for approx. 1 hour
Heavier housework (washing floors vacuuming etc.) for approx. ½ hour continuously
Sitting in bed for approx. ½ hour
Walking between approx. 100m and 1km on level ground (length of 1 to 10 football fields)
Sitting in an upright chair (dining chair) with feet on floor for approx. 2 hours
Reading and understanding a non-fiction text such as an official document one page long
Participating in a conversation with three people for approx. ½ hour
Staying outdoors in daylight without sunglasses for approx. 2 hours
Focusing on a task for approx. 10 minutes continuously
Cooking a complicated meal from scratch approx. 1 hour of preparation
Using social media to stay in touch with others
